{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "There needs to be clearer standards of appropriate versus inappropriate uses of generative text capabilities.",
    "Existing studies indicate that without proper ethical usage training, academic integrity remains a major concern for students adopting AI in their education (Sullivan et al., 2023; Cotton et al., 2023; Rudolph et al., 2023).",
    "Students are inclined to utilize the text-generation capabilities of systems like ChatGPT to complete essay assignments or even online exams (Susnjak, 2022).",
    "This concern has intensified with empirical findings revealing that current AI detection methods have not proven effective at identifying AI-generated content (Davis & Kumar, 2023).",
    "Dependence on AI for content risks diminishing original analysis, and critical thinking is needed to engage deeply with course material (Townsend & Hunt, 2019; Rudolph et al., 2023)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Existing studies indicate that without proper ethical usage training, academic integrity remains a major concern for students adopting AI in their education (Sullivan et al., 2023; Cotton et al., 2023; Rudolph et al., 2023).",
